io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.services.impl

Class NativeThreadPoolScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.services.impl.AbstractScheduler<ScheduledFuture<?>>
      • io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.services.impl.NativeThreadPoolScheduler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPlatformScheduler

    @Singleton
public class NativeThreadPoolScheduler
extends AbstractScheduler<ScheduledFuture<?>>
implements IPlatformScheduler
    Implements a Java ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor based scheduler to schedule a synchronization job.

    for every job, an independent, new event creating Runnable is added to the queue. This new Runnable does create a new Thread and makes it execute the scheduled job. So for every job execution, a new thread is created. This helps to avoid blocking the timer queue by long running threads. A crashing thread will not affect the timer, too.

      • scheduleAtFixedRate

        public String scheduleAtFixedRate(Runnable job,
                                  long period)
        Description copied from interface: IPlatformScheduler
        Schedule a re-occurring job with a timer at a fixed timing rate.

        Starting from this very millisecond, the job is executed after every period milliseconds have passed. period is also used as initial delay. So in case it is set to one hour (= 3600000 milliseconds), the job is first executed in an hour and then every hour afterwards.

        There is no check whether the same instance is added again.

        Specified by:
        scheduleAtFixedRate in interface IPlatformScheduler
        Parameters:
        job - the runnable to to execute. In case it is null, the schedule is ignored.
        period - the period in milliseconds to execute the job.
        Returns:
        a key to the scheduled job, that can be used to remove the schedule later with IPlatformScheduler.stopSchedule(String).

      • cancel

        public IPlatformScheduler cancel()
        Description copied from interface: IPlatformScheduler
        Cancel all queued scheduled jobs and terminate the timer threads as soon as possible.

        The currently running job is not terminated. Only the queue is cleared and all schedules cancelled.

        Specified by:
        cancel in interface IPlatformScheduler
        Returns:
        this to support Fluent Interface.
